<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1540,2084]" box="[189,938,1644,1668]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Etymology. The specific name is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[730,776,1644,1668]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
locality; noun.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1540,2084]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Li" authorityName="Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2019" box="[615,802,1678,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuyapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[615,717,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. cuyapo</emphasis>
Li &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[807,891,1679,1703]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[807,891,1679,1703]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but can be distinguished by the very short copulatory duct that connects the spermathecae to the afferent spermathecae and the size of the spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1298,1713,1737]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Li" authorityName="Li &amp; Li" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuyapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1316,1420,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. cuyapo</emphasis>
Li &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[194,279,1748,1772]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[194,279,1748,1772]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a long, curved copulatory duct and small spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[929,1029,1748,1772]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="27.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-54@27.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 20. Speocera cuyapo Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366963/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1540,2084]" lastBlockId="26.[136,707,236,330]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Description. Female. Total length 1.08; carapace length 0.50; carapace width 0.41; abdomen length 0.53; abdomen width 0.42. Prosoma: carapace pyriform, narrowing gradually anteriorly; light yellow, slightly suffused with purplish pattern (
<figureCitation box="[144,243,1852,1876]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
); pars cephalica flat; fovea not visible. Sternum light yellow, suffused with purplish color, as long as wide (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Endites light yellow with serrula; labium light yellow. Clypeus nearly vertical; short. Chelicerae light yellow; promargin with a series of six teeth reaching the lamina; retromargin with two very small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1332,1921,1945]" captionStart="Figure 58" captionStartId="73.[154,217,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,233,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-98@73.[188,1398,233,2011]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figure 58. Female chelicerae of Speocera spp., anterior view. A. S. balikpapan Li &amp; Li sp. nov. B. S. batang Li &amp; Li sp. nov. C. S. bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov. D. S. cuyapo Li &amp; Li sp. nov. E. S. dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov. F. S. griswoldi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. G. S. huifengi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. H. S. huisun Li &amp; Li sp. nov. I. S. melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov. J. S. tabuk Li &amp; Li sp. nov. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367045/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 58E</figureCitation>
). Eyes: six contiguous eyes, nearly equal sized, surrounded by black pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[911,1010,1956,1980]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma oval; purplish (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1440,1956,1980]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Legs light yellow; leg formula 4123; leg lengths I 1.72 (0.49, 0.15, 0.50, 0.31, 0.27); 
<collectionCode box="[1057,1075,1991,2014]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">II</collectionCode>
1.57 (0.45, 0.15, 0.43, 0.29, 0.25); 
<collectionCode box="[136,163,2026,2049]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">III</collectionCode>
1.34 (0.38, 0.13, 0.33, 0.28, 0.23); 
<collectionCode box="[568,596,2026,2049]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">IV</collectionCode>
1.82 (0.50, 0.16, 0.51, 0.38, 0.28). Genitalia. Internal genitalia with afferent spermathecae short, straight, tip slightly curved posteriorly, not extending past the sides of the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1438,2060,2084]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 21B</figureCitation>
); spermathecae large, spherical (
<figureCitation box="[465,564,236,261]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="28.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figure 21. Speocera dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366965/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[136,707,236,330]" box="[189,370,271,295]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[136,707,236,330]" box="[189,707,306,330]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
